            <LEXSense LanguageCode="en" LastEdited="2021-10-14 11:31:54" LastEditedBy="">
              <DefinitionLong/>
              <DefinitionShort>(a figurative extension of meaning of {L:κολαφίζω&lt;SDBG:κολαφίζω:000000&gt;}[a] ‘to beat with the fist,’ {D:19.7}) to cause injury or weakness or possibly a circumstantial difficulty</DefinitionShort>
              <Glosses>
                <Gloss>to cause harm to</Gloss>
              </Glosses>
              <Comments>Though differences of interpretation exist concerning the meaning of ‘a thorn in my flesh’ ({S:04701200700038}), especially since some scholars have felt that this must refer to some kind of physical disability, it seems more likely to assume that it refers to some special personal circumstance such as the opposition Paul encountered in preaching the gospel, a reference suggested by {S:04701201000000} (see also {D:22.20}).|Without some clear understanding of the reference of ‘a thorn in my flesh,’ it is difficult to determine precisely how κολαφίζω is to be interpreted in {S:04701200700038}.</Comments>
